73. Develop a PHP program to display an error message when a file other than jpg or png is uploaded.
ANSWER
<?php
if ($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] == 'POST') {
    if (isset($_FILES['image'])) {
        $fileName = $_FILES['image']['name'];
        $fileTmp = $_FILES['image']['tmp_name'];

        // Get the file extension
        $fileExt = strtolower(pathinfo($fileName, PATHINFO_EXTENSION));

        // Allowed extensions
        $allowed = ['jpg', 'jpeg', 'png'];

        if (in_array($fileExt, $allowed)) {
            echo "File is valid: $fileName";
            // You can save the file with move_uploaded_file() if needed
        } else {
            echo "Error: Only JPG and PNG files are allowed!";
        }
    } else {
        echo "No file uploaded.";
    }
}
?>
<!-- Simple HTML form -->
<form method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
    Select image to upload (JPG/PNG only):
    <input type="file" name="image" required>
    <input type="submit" value="Upload">
</form>

OUTPUT
File is valid: program 72.png
Select image to upload (JPG/PNG only): No file chosen 
